# problem-specific runtime parameters
#
# CR_Streaming_Test : initial-condition geometry (Jiang & Oh 2018, Section 4)
#    0 = 1D triangular Ec profile       (Sec 4.1.1, Fig. 3)         <-- this directory (streaming)
#    1 = 1D Gaussian Ec profile         (Sec 4.1.1 / 4.1.4)         <-- switch here for the Gaussian streaming test (Fig. 1)
#    2 = 2D Gaussian Ec, diagonal B     (Sec 4.1.2 / 4.1.5)
#    3 = 2D ring Ec, circular B         (Sec 4.1.5)
#    4 = 1D density cloud (bottleneck)  (Sec 4.1.3)
#    5 = 1D CR-driven wave              (Sec 4.2.1)
#    6 = 2D CR-driven blast wave        (Sec 4.2.3)
# --> the CR physics parameters (CR_SIGMA, CR_STREAM, CR_SOURCE, ...) come from Input__Parameter
#
CR_Streaming_Test        0              # 0=triangular (default), 1=Gaussian streaming
CR_Streaming_Dir         0              # streaming/diffusion axis for the 1D tests (0/1/2 = x/y/z)
CR_Streaming_FlowV       0.0            # uniform background flow velocity along CR_Streaming_Dir
